question:
Each of $\triangle PQR$ and $\triangle STU$ has an area of $1.$ In $\triangle PQR,$ $U,$ $W,$ and $V$ are the midpoints of the sides. In $\triangle STU,$ $R,$ $V,$ and $W$ are the midpoints of the sides. What is the area of parallelogram $UVRW?$ [asy]
draw((0,0)--(2,0)--(1,2)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,2)--(2,2)--(1,0)--cycle,linewidth(1));
label("$T$",(0,0),SW);
label("$R$",(1,0),S);
label("$S$",(2,0),SE);
label("$W$",(1.5,1),E);
label("$Q$",(2,2),NE);
label("$U$",(1,2),N);
label("$P$",(0,2),NW);
label("$V$",(0.5,1),W);
[/asy]

agents_response:
The area of $\triangle PQR$ can be expressed as $\frac{1}{2}(PQ)(QR)$ and the area of $\triangle STU$ as $\frac{1}{2}(SU)(UT).$ Notice that $VR=\frac{1}{2}PQ$ and $UW=\frac{1}{2}QR$ while $VW=\frac{1}{2}SU$ and $RU=\frac{1}{2}UT.$ Thus the area of the parallelogram is $\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^2\cdot 2\cdot \left(\frac{1}{2}PQ\cdot QR\right)=\frac{1}{4},$ so the answer is $\boxed{\frac{1}{4}}.$ [asy]
draw((0,0)--(2,0)--(1,2)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,2)--(2,2)--(1,0)--cycle,linewidth(1));
label("$T$",(0,0),SW);
label("$R$",(1,0),S);
label("$S$",(2,0),SE);
label("$W$",(1.5,1),E);
label("$Q$",(2,2),NE);
label("$U$",(1,2),N);
label("$P$",(0,2),NW);
label("$V$",(0.5,1),W);
[/asy]
